    • Method Detail

      • max

        public static <T> T max(Collection<? extends T> coll,
                        Comparator<? super T> cmp)
        Finds maximum element in a collection using a comparator. This implementation differs from its overloaded counterpart max(Collection<? extends T> coll) only in its comparison. The other method uses compareTo(T t) rather than compare(T t1, T t2).
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of element in collection
        Parameters:
        coll - collection providing elements
        cmp - comparator consuming elements used for ordering
        Returns:
        maximum element from collection
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - when null parameters are passed

      • reverseOrder

        public static <T> Comparator<T> reverseOrder(Comparator<T> cmp)
        Reverses the order of the comparator parameter. Unlike reverseOrder(), this This implementation constructs a new comparator with the old comparator like cmp.compare(o2, o1). Rather than calling o1.compareTo(o2).
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of element in collection
        Parameters:
        cmp - comparator being reversed
        Returns:
        reverse order comparator of parameter
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - when null parameters are passed
